pulltitle: Don't embed a scrollable container within another scrollable container, Resolves #239
pullsbody:
We currently embed a ```ListView``` within a ```ScrollView``` this is not optimal since both view containers have their own handlers for scrolling. Additionally, it's bad for performance as it forces the ListView to load all of it's contents, instead of functioning properly and efficiently.

See: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ScrollView.html

Closes: #239
pull_repo_desc: :mag: Digital Skills Observatory: Software Prototype I
pull_commit_message: Don't embed a scrollable container within another scrollable container, Resolves #239

pulltitle: Use layout weight to scale welcome image based on available screen space
pullsbody:
This is not a permanent fix. The permanent fix would be to create multiple layouts or define some sort of ruleset for scaling everything accordingly. This just uses layout weight to scale the welcome image based on available screen space, and doesn't effect any other UI components on the view.

A quick fix needs to be implemented in order to meet the release schedule, additionally this issue of poor scaling is wide spread throughout the app and requires additional attention. This will most likely be dealt with as work apart of a larger app redesign.

Related: #224

pullsbody:
This was the first step out of a multi-step process to finish work towards modernizing the Jisort code base, the goal is to have a heavy focus on minimalism (if you don't need it, don't write it).

First round of code cleanup was very effective, on average you can expect anywhere from a 10 to 15 MB reduction on the APK size (and unpacked), newer phones with larger displays are likely to see the highest reduction in app size, but all users should benefit from these changes.

Edit: The APK size reduction changes have been moved to a separate PR (merged into master) for the sake of making the other changes easy to read and review.
